import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

data = pd.read_csv("GameStats.csv", delimiter = ',')
data["Level"] = data["Level"].apply(lambda x: float(x[6:]))
data["NumBlocks"] = data["NumBlocks"].apply(lambda x: float(x))
data["Score"] = data["Score"].apply(lambda x: float(x))
data["IsWin"] = data["IsWin"].replace({True : 1, False : 0})
data = data[["Level", "NumBlocks", "ElapsedTime", "Score", "Accuracy", "IsWin"]]

print(data.head())

In [57]:
import numpy as np
from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Dense
from tensorflow.keras.callbacks import EarlyStopping, ModelCheckpoint
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn import metrics
import pandas as pd

class AccAndLoss:
    def __init__(self, train_acc, valid_acc, train_loss, valid_loss):
        self.train_acc = train_acc
        self.valid_acc = valid_acc
        self.train_loss = train_loss
        self.valid_loss = valid_loss

class ModelData:
    
    dataset : np.ndarray
    XVALID : np.ndarray
    YVALID : np.ndarray
    XTRAIN : np.ndarray
    YTRAIN : np.ndarray
    model : Sequential
       
    layers = 0
    neurons = 0
    neuronRatio = 0
    batchSize = 0
    epochs = 0
    optimizer = 0
    activation = 0

    def getLayers(self):
        return self.layers
    def getNeurons(self):
        return self.neurons
    def getNeuronRatio(self):
        return self.neuronRatio
    def getBatchSize(self):
        return self.batchSize
    def getEpochs(self):
        return self.epochs
    def getOptimizer(self):
        return self.optimizer
    def getActivation(self):
        return self.activation
    
    
    def setHyperParameters(self, layers, neurons, neuronRatio, batchSize, epochs, optimizer, activation):
        self.layers = layers
        self.neurons = neurons
        self.neuronRatio = neuronRatio
        self.batchSize = batchSize
        self.epochs = epochs
        self.optimizer = optimizer
        self.activation = activation
    
    def __init__(self, dataset):
        self.dataset = dataset
        self.setData()
        
    def setData(self, printShape = False):
        np.random.shuffle(self.dataset)

        idx = int(0.3 * len(self.dataset[:, 0]))
        
        self.XVALID = self.dataset[:idx, range(len(dataset[0]) - 1)]
        self.YVALID = self.dataset[:idx, [len(dataset[0]) - 1]]
        self.XTRAIN = self.dataset[idx:, range(len(dataset[0]) - 1)]
        self.YTRAIN = self.dataset[idx:, [len(dataset[0]) - 1]]
        
        # normalize
        mean = self.XTRAIN.mean(axis=0)
        self.XTRAIN -= mean
        std = self.XTRAIN.std(axis=0)
        self.XTRAIN /= std
        
        self.XVALID -= mean
        self.XVALID /= std
        
        if (printShape):
            print(self.XVALID.shape)
            print(self.YVALID.shape)
            print(self.XTRAIN.shape)
            print(self.YTRAIN.shape)
        
    def setModel(self, printSummary = False):
        self.model = Sequential()
    
        neuronCount = self.getNeurons()

        self.model.add(Dense(neuronCount, input_dim = len(self.XTRAIN[0, :]), activation=self.getActivation()))
        for i in range(self.getLayers() - 2):
            neuronCount -= neuronCount * self.getNeuronRatio()
            self.model.add(Dense(neuronCount, activation=self.getActivation()))
        self.model.add(Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))

        self.model.compile(loss = 'BinaryCrossentropy', optimizer = self.getOptimizer(), metrics=['accuracy'])
        
        if (printSummary):
            print(self.model.summary())
            
    
    def run(self, verbose = 0, name="default"):

        history = self.model.fit(self.XTRAIN, self.YTRAIN, validation_data = (self.XVALID, self.YVALID), batch_size = self.getBatchSize(), epochs = self.getEpochs(), verbose = verbose)

        y_pred_train = self.model.predict(self.XTRAIN)
        y_pred_train_rounded = y_pred_train.round()
        y_pred = self.model.predict(self.XVALID)
        y_pred_rounded = y_pred.round()

        tAcc = metrics.accuracy_score(self.YTRAIN, y_pred_train_rounded)
        vAcc = metrics.accuracy_score(self.YVALID, y_pred_rounded)
        tLoss = metrics.log_loss(self.YTRAIN, y_pred_train)
        vLoss = metrics.log_loss(self.YVALID, y_pred)
        df_metrics = pd.DataFrame([[tAcc, vAcc, tLoss,vLoss]], columns=["Train Accuracy", "Valid Accuracy", "Train Loss", "Valid Loss"])

        tableOutputFile = open("metricsOutput.txt", "a")
        tableOutputFile.write("%s:\n" % name)
        tableOutputFile.write(df_metrics.style.to_latex())
        tableOutputFile.write("\n")
        tableOutputFile.close()
        print(df_metrics)
        
        return AccAndLoss(tAcc, vAcc, tLoss, vLoss)

# only Level
dataset = data[["Level", "IsWin"]].values
np.random.shuffle(dataset)

print(dataset[:5])

print(len(dataset[0]))

mData = ModelData(dataset)

mData.setData(printShape=True)

layers = 3
neurons = 32
neuronRatio = 0.75
batchSize = 256
epochs = 256
optimizer = "rmsprop"
activation = "relu"

mData.setHyperParameters(layers, neurons, neuronRatio, batchSize, epochs, optimizer, activation)
mData.setModel(printSummary=True)

accLevel = mData.run(verbose=1, name="onlyLevel")

print("Level: %f" % accLevel.valid_acc)

dataset = data[["NumBlocks", "IsWin"]].values
np.random.shuffle(dataset)

neuronRatio = 0.75
batchSize = 256
epochs = 256

activation = "relu"

mData.setModel(printSummary=True)

accNumBlocks = mData.run(verbose=1, name="onlyNumBlocks")

print("NumBlocks: %f" % accNumBlocks.valid_acc)

# only ElapsedTime
dataset = data[["ElapsedTime", "IsWin"]].values
np.random.shuffle(dataset)

print(dataset[:5])

print(len(dataset[0]))

mData = ModelData(dataset)

mData.setData(printShape=True)

layers = 3
neurons = 32
neuronRatio = 0.75
batchSize = 256
epochs = 256
optimizer = "rmsprop"
activation = "relu"

mData.setHyperParameters(layers, neurons, neuronRatio, batchSize, epochs, optimizer, activation)
mData.setModel(printSummary=True)

accElapsedTime = mData.run(verbose=1, name="onlyElapsedTime")

print("ElapsedTime: %f" % accElapsedTime.valid_acc)

# only Score
dataset = data[["Score", "IsWin"]].values
np.random.shuffle(dataset)

print(dataset[:5])

print(len(dataset[0]))

mData = ModelData(dataset)

mData.setData(printShape=True)

layers = 3
neurons = 32
neuronRatio = 0.75
batchSize = 256
epochs = 256
optimizer = "rmsprop"
activation = "relu"

mData.setHyperParameters(layers, neurons, neuronRatio, batchSize, epochs, optimizer, activation)
mData.setModel(printSummary=True)

accScore = mData.run(verbose=1, name="onlyScore")

print("Score: %f" % accScore.valid_acc)

# only Accuracy
dataset = data[["Accuracy", "IsWin"]].values
np.random.shuffle(dataset)

print(dataset[:5])

print(len(dataset[0]))

mData = ModelData(dataset)

mData.setData(printShape=True)

layers = 3
neurons = 32
neuronRatio = 0.75
batchSize = 256
epochs = 256
optimizer = "rmsprop"
activation = "relu"

mData.setHyperParameters(layers, neurons, neuronRatio, batchSize, epochs, optimizer, activation)
mData.setModel(printSummary=True)

accAccuracy = mData.run(verbose=1, name="onlyAccuracy")

print("Accuracy: %f" % accAccuracy.valid_acc)

# removed only ElapsedTime
dataset = data[["Level", "NumBlocks", "Score", "Accuracy", "IsWin"]].values
np.random.shuffle(dataset)

print(dataset[:5])

print(len(dataset[0]))

mData = ModelData(dataset)

mData.setData(printShape=True)

layers = 3
neurons = 32
neuronRatio = 0.75
batchSize = 256
epochs = 256
optimizer = "rmsprop"
activation = "relu"

mData.setHyperParameters(layers, neurons, neuronRatio, batchSize, epochs, optimizer, activation)
mData.setModel(printSummary=True)

accR1 = mData.run(verbose=1, name="noElapsedTime")

print("Removed ElapsedTime: %f" % accR1.valid_acc)

dataset = data[["Level", "Score", "Accuracy", "IsWin"]].values
np.random.shuffle(dataset)

print(dataset[:5])

print(len(dataset[0]))

mData = ModelData(dataset)

mData.setData(printShape=True)

layers = 3
neurons = 32
neuronRatio = 0.75
batchSize = 256
epochs = 256
optimizer = "rmsprop"
activation = "relu"

mData.setHyperParameters(layers, neurons, neuronRatio, batchSize, epochs, optimizer, activation)
mData.setModel(printSummary=True)

accR2 = mData.run(verbose=1, name="noElapsedTimeNumBlocks")

print("Removed ElapsedTime and NumBlocks: %f" % accR2.valid_acc)

# All features model
dataset = data.values
np.random.shuffle(dataset)

print(dataset[:5])

print(len(dataset[0]))

mData = ModelData(dataset)

mData.setData(printShape=True)

layers = 3
neurons = 32
neuronRatio = 0.75
batchSize = 256
epochs = 256
optimizer = "rmsprop"
activation = "relu"

mData.setHyperParameters(layers, neurons, neuronRatio, batchSize, epochs, optimizer, activation)
mData.setModel(printSummary=True)

accAll = mData.run(verbose=1, name="allFeatures")

print("All features: %f" % accAll.valid_acc)

from pandas import Series, DataFrame

barData = [accLevel.valid_acc, accNumBlocks.valid_acc, accElapsedTime.valid_acc, accScore.valid_acc, accAccuracy.valid_acc, accR1.valid_acc, accR2.valid_acc, accR3.valid_acc, accAll.valid_acc]
barLabels = ['Only Level', 'Only NumBlocks', 'Only ElapsedTime', 'Only Score', 'Only Accuracy', 'No ElapsedTime', 'No ElapsedTime, NumBlocks', 'No ElapsedTime, NumBlocks, Level', "All Features"]

# modified from https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/python-program-for-bubble-sort/
def bubbleSort(arr, arr1):
    n = len(arr)
 
    # Traverse through all array elements
    for i in range(n-1):
    # range(n) also work but outer loop will
    # repeat one time more than needed.
 
        # Last i elements are already in place
        for j in range(0, n-i-1):
 
            # traverse the array from 0 to n-i-1
            # Swap if the element found is greater
            # than the next element
            if arr[j] > arr[j + 1] :
                arr[j], arr[j + 1] = arr[j + 1], arr[j]
                arr1[j], arr1[j + 1] = arr1[j + 1], arr1[j]

bubbleSort(barData, barLabels)

plt.xticks(range(len(barData)), barLabels, rotation=75)
plt.xlabel("Test")
plt.ylabel("Accuracy")
plt.ylim(0.5, 0.95)
plt.title("All Tests")
plt.bar(range(len(barData)), barData)
plt.show()
